channel.title: Path not specified
channel.description:
Yo Moparscapers.
So I decided to download OSRemake's source and check it out, but it just comes with with Path not specified. Press any key to continue.
I know that usually means that the Java's path is dodgy but it was working before.
I used Lin's Java EV setter too. Any idea's?
C:\Program Files\Common Files\Microsoft Shared\Windows Live;C:\windows\system32;C:\windows;C:\windows\System32\Wbem;C:\WINDOWS\system32\WindowsPowerShell\v1.0;C:\Program Files\Common Files\Ulead Systems\MPEG;C:\Program Files\QuickTime\QTSystem\;C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_17\bin\;C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_17\bin\;C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_17\bin\;
That's in the Java EV setter. It looks like it's trying to use half my program files but I can't edit it.
[br][br][size=1]Posted on: December 08, 2009, 04:25:47 pm[/size][hr]Anyone?
